<br>
Mithaniel - &quot;His followers strive to rid Norrath of all things dark and evil&quot;....&quot;They will not rest until the day when all of Norrath is cleansed in Mithaniel's light&quot;.<br>
<br>
Rodcet Nife - &quot;They are not content to deal with the effects of disease and death after they occur and vigorously seek to destroy the sources of these evils.&quot;<br>
<br>
-taken from the deity descriptions at character creation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/1/02 12:38:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16161.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which deity would be most in opposition to Undead?</span><hr size=1> My take on the paladin gods and their views toward the undead.<br>
<br>
Rodcet Nife is the God of Life, the Prime Healer.  As such unlife (i.e. undead) and disease are by their very definitions antithesis to all that he represents.<br>
<br>
Tunare is the Goddess of Nature. Undead and summoned creatures are diametically opposed to her ideals.<br>
<br>
Quellious is the Goddess of Tranquility.  The torturing of souls which is necessary to create undead would be abhorrent to her as it distrupts the tranquility of the cycle of life.<br>
<br>
E Marr is the Goddess of Love.  The creation of undead is certainly one of the most hateful acts in creation which would be anathema to her.<br>
<br>
M Marr is the God of Valor.  Undead are created by cowards that are unwilling to face their foes with honor and thus depend the powers of darkness to fullfill their ends.<br>
<br>
Karana is the God of Storms, the Rainmaker.  His rain brings fertility to the crops which sustain his worshipers.  Undead can not contribute to the fertility of the land, and thus should be washed away by his storms.<br>
<br>
Prexus is the God of Water and the Seas.  The oceans were the cradle of life. The place where it first flourished.  Undead are the abomination of that which he nurtured, and his followers should endevor to rid the world of their blight.<br>
<br>
Brell is the God of Earth.  The dead are buried within his arms.  To raise the dead, is rip away the souls that have been entrusted to his protection.  He seeks to recover those whose souls were stolen.  But, woe to those that cross Brell Serilis by the creation of such abominations.<br>
<br>
Bristlebane is the prankster god.  He loves freedom and a good joke.  The undead have no soul and as such have no sense of humor.  Their's is a facsimili of life which is controlled by another who's immorality is the ultimate tyranny. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
Seventh Cavalry<BR>
