<br>
1) Created - those created directly by necromatic magic. I'd also put vampires and any other undead that can create more of its own kind in this catagory.<br>
<br>
2) &quot;Natural&quot; occuring - Typically seen as those who die with some unresolved business. Lots of restless ghosts fit this category, but some skeletal undead and all revenants fit this catagory.<br>
<br>
3) hybrid of 1 &amp; 2 - Though not intentionally created for some specific task, the dead sometimes rise in places with evil taint.<br>
<br>
Of all the deities, Nife is the one whom I would see wanted 1 &amp; 3 destroyed, and 2 put to rest. I can see a paladin or cleric of Nife going out of her way to resolve a haunting.<br>
<br>
I could also see a Tunare paladin wanting to do this, but not as dedicated to it, so i would put her second. #3s would be a big issue for her.<br>
<br>
Mithaniel's clerigy probably wouldn't be too conserned with #2 unless they where destructive in nature, but would really want to destroy 1 &amp; 3, so I put him third.<br>
