<br>
The reason for my ranking is that Tunare simply is not described as an active god.  She is concerned with her elves, and the nurturing of life, esp woodland lifeforms but simply doesn't appear to be a proactive force in anyway.  The other two deities and their followers are *active* combatants.<br>
<br>
There could be hoards of undead in some mountain area and it seems Tunare wouldn't care one way of the other where as rodcet and mith marr would set out to bring their version of righteousness to the area.<br>
<br>
In *theory* I could see the rankings as Tunare/Rodcet/Mith Marr as undead are beyond life and can not be 'healed' in any fashion.  However, undead are removed from the natural order of life/decay/rebirth and as such are a hinderance to the natural order of things.  But given the descriptions of the deities Tunare's focus is actually fairly narrow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/2/02 4:47:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16161.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which deity would be most in opposition to Undead?</span><hr size=1> Tunarian Clerics are given a quest at level one to destroy the invading undead o Innoruk in Great Faydark. While Tunare is more of a conceptual god being as she is sort of a primal foirce of nature more than a deity, she is concerned with the destruction of Undead as are all the good gods.<br>
<br>
That Said I would rank Rodcet Nife as top of the list for Undead Hunters. MOST undead in Norrath can have their origin's traced to Bertoxxulous and Nife an Bertoxx have an undying war with each other of the higherst order.<br>
<br>
The way I see it, Rodcet Nife is top of the list with pretty much all the other 'good' gods second and roughly equal in there urge to destroy undead. Mith Marr, being a god of Valor and Truth is battle centric so ANYTHING involving combat will involve him and sinec all undead are pretty evil and unnatural we do them a lot.<br>
