<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bertoxxulous  ·  The Plaguebringer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead? Yea baby! Let's make more of them! WOOT! Party On! *starts dancing* Undead party in my plane!!!!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Brell Serilis  ·  The Duke of Below</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I LOVE THE DIRT!!!!!! All my followers love the dirt too. So much so that they show their devotion to me by living underground in caves, caverns and tunnels. Did I mention that I'm all about the dirt. Oh, you were asking me about undead. *looks about confused for a moment* I really don't have an undead problem down here. That's more of an issue for those above grounders to deal with.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bristlebane  ·  The King of Thieves</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
You know Grieg Veneficus right? Yea well he used to be a white ghost. That was until I put purple die in his shampoo. I really didn't mean for it to be a perminate thing, but you know how these pranks are in that they don't always work out. Then there were these Undead Shissar. Well I one of my pranks backfired so much that that they're not even undead. Opps. Paladins are kinda peeved on that, so don't tell them it was me ok. And then there is Maid Isis... *continues to talk for hours about various tricks and pranks he pulled on various undead.*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Cazic-Thule  ·  The Faceless</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Do I look scary to you? I just got in some new Tentacle Tormentors an hour ago. What do you think? Does it make you tremble in fear? What about my lioncloth. Does it scare you? RAAR! Oh you wish to know about the undead? Well, I like undead cause they scare the kids. I don't like that Irak fellow who's been haning about my plane though, but I do have fun scaring him. Think I'll go chace him around some. Got to go. *Cazic-Thule waves bye*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> E`ci  ·  The Wintry Guardian</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Isn't ice nice... Oh, you wish to ask me about undead. I don't really have time for that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Erollisi Marr  ·  The Queen of Love</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Like sometimes when a person dies y'know, their love is like just so awesome that their spirit refuses to rest. They so totally want to make sure that their loved ones are safe and well, y'know.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Fennin Ro  ·  The Tyrant of Fire</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead? I care not about these creatures you speak of. Fire is everything and all that truely matters. *sets fire to a pool of lava to prove his point*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Innoruuk  ·  The Prince of Hate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I HATE UNDEAD! I hate you! I hate that guy over there! I hate the message board you interviewing me for! I hate everyone! I hate Hate!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Karana  ·  The Rain Keeper</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Well I have more pressing matters to worry about right now than some pesky undead. See my plane was taken over recently, so I'm kinda busy recriting heros to assist me reclaim it. You wouldn't happen to be a hero or know any?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Mithaniel Marr  ·  The Truthbringer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
*said with a sterotypical hero voice* Let us bring good and rightousness to the lands by cleansing away all that is bad and evil. I wish my really hot sister wasn't such a ditz. *finally notices the question* Is it an evil undead?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Povar  ·  The Veiled One</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
*does not appear to notice the question and does not respond to it*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Prexus  ·  The Ocean Lord</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead really are more of a land dweller issue. Sure I get a few of them, but if these undead are willing to defend the oceans and sease from harm, then I welcome them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Quellious  ·  The Tranquil</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I feel sorry for the undead ones. Perhaps one of my followers will aid them in finding inner peace.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rallos Zek  ·  The Warlord</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead are gross man. I'm all about chowing down on fallen enemies, but who want's to eat a smelly rotting corpse.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rodcet Nife  ·  The Prime Healer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
There are several problems with undead. First they go around attacking people at random for no good reason, and secondly they tend to spread diseases. Now, if we could train the undead to stop attacking people, we can then find a way to cure them of both their disease and their undead state. I really would prefer not to see more dead bodies being made.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Solusek Ro  ·  The Burning Prince</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Hi there! *smiles and shakes hands* Undead? I don't really care either way. Did Mithaniel say anything about me when you talked to him?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Tarew Marr  ·  The Fathom Lord, Ruler of the Triumvirate of Water</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Yes well, undead doesn't really apply to what I do here.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Terris-Thule  ·  The Dream Scorcher</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead are fun and hordes of them make for good nightmares.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Nameless</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
*could not be reached for questioning*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Rathe  ·  The Council</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Undead are very messy and chaotic. We don't really care for that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Tribunal  ·  The Council of Justice</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If the undead have done anything wrong, they will be brought before us for judgement.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Tunare  ·  The Mother of All</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I am the goddess of the elves and of nature. The undead are unnatural... abominations which must be destroyed so that life may flourish.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Veeshan  ·  The Mother of all Wurms</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
When the stars are right, I will reclaim this world for my children. All who oppose me, undead or not will be destroyed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Xegony  ·  The Queen of Air</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I'm sure they're not all bad. Perhaps if we ask them nicely, they will behave themselves.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
So which deity do I think is the most opposed to the undead. Clearly Innoruuk as he's the one one who outright hates them.<br>
